OL,3,CThousands take part in Town and Gown
OL,4,CRun
OL,6,F"It brings people from Oxfordshire
OL,7,Ftogether to support Muscular Dystrophy
OL,8,FUK.
OL,10,F"The funds raised will help us to
OL,11,Fcontinue funding groundbreaking
OL,12,Fresearch and support those living with
OL,13,Fa muscle wasting and weakening
OL,14,Fcondition."
OL,16,FThe first 10k runner across the finish
OL,17,Fline was Alex Brampton who ran the
OL,18,Fcourse with a chip time of 31:23. The
OL,19,Ffastest female was Katy Ward with a
OL,20,Fchip time of 36:23.
